
                                            Solidarity members, including flight captains, are to go on strike from Monday morning after wage negotiations with Mango Airlines fell flat on Sunday night.
                                         JOHANNESBURG – Solidarity members, including flight captains, are to go on strike from Monday morning after wage negotiations with Mango Airlines fell flat on Sunday night. Solidarity members, which represents 95% of the pilots at the low-cost Mango airline, will go on strike as from 5am Monday morning. This comes after the trade union met with Mango’s management to reach a possible settlement in salary negotiations. #MangoStrike Solidarity's Deon Reyneke says according to their information no Mango airline pilot reported for duty at OR Tambo airport. 